node.text: Available now! Lucky Holler Hazy IPA combines Citra, Simcoe and Galaxy hops. The backbone of this beer is built with malted oats, pale malt, unmalted wheat and white wheat. That provides Lucky Holler's hazy profile, propping up oils that would typically fall out during fermentation. “The haze acts like a hop-oil delivery system to your palate," says brewmaster John Trogner. Tune in to Christie for the flavor profile, and find Lucky Holler near you at troegs.com/brewfinder! #LuckyHoller #Troegs #HazyIPA #PAbeer

node.text: "This beer is a perfect example of why I do what I do," says @DeerCreekMalt's Mark Brault in the latest episode of @PouredinPA. He was talking about Scratch #430, the Spelt Golden Lager we brewed together. "Our goal is to bring consumers closer to the farm and the farmers who grow grain. Teach people that beer is an agricultural product, not a commodity. And to try to make a meaningful beverage that has a story and builds community. This project did all of those things." Check out the episode! #PAbeer #PouredinPA

node.text: Available now! Lucky Holler Hazy IPA combines Citra, Simcoe and Galaxy hops. The backbone of this beer is built with malted oats, pale malt, unmalted wheat and white wheat. That provides Lucky Holler's hazy profile, propping up oils that would typically fall out during fermentation. “The haze acts like a hop-oil delivery system to your palate," says brewmaster John Trogner. Tune in to Christie for the flavor profile, and find Lucky Holler near you at troegs.com/brewfinder! #LuckyHoller #Troegs #HazyIPA #PAbeer

node.text: Today's the day our Pennsylvania Peach whiskey collab with @WigleWhiskey is available! If you're in Pittsburgh, you can pick it up on Smallman Street or at Ross Park Mall. If you're anywhere else in PA or DC, you can have it shipped right to your door. Pennsylvania Peach starts with Wigle's made-from-scratch whiskey distilled from regionally grown organic wheat grain. For four years, the folks at Wigle aged the whiskey in new charred oak barrels, then transferred it to barrels that once housed our Freaky Peach Pennsylvania Sour Ale. Finally, the whiskey was steeped with peaches and apricots. We taste: notes of peach, mango, brown sugar and allspice. To celebrate this partnership, we're donating $1 from each bottle to @FeedingPA's win-win mission of connecting food-insecure Pennsylvanians with surplus from local farms. #linkinbio to order. And if you're local to Tröegs, you can get a taste in early September with a Wigle pop-up here at the brewery. Stay tuned for details! #Whiskey #WigleWhiskey #Troegs #Cocktails #Beer #Pittsburgh

node.text: Don't miss Perpetual Haze! Another run of cans is coming this Thursday here at the brewery. We've taken the clean, crisp bitterness of a West Coast IPA and combined it with the softness of a hazy. Raw wheat, London-3 yeast and vigorous dry-hopping stir up a haze that cradles the citrusy hop combination. Front and center are Citra and Cashmere, unlocking juicy notes of orange, passionfruit and nectarine. See you at the brewery soon! #Troegs #PABeer #PerpetualHaze #Hershey

node.text: Here at Tröegs, this is what collaboration is all about. Finding fellow family-owned Pennsylvania makers and working together to create a great new taste. Pennsylvania Peach is our first collaboration with Pittsburgh's @WigleWhiskey, and it's all about peaches. It starts with Wigle's made-from-scratch whiskey distilled from regionally grown organic wheat grain. For four years, the folks at Wigle aged the whiskey in new charred oak barrels, then transferred it to barrels that once housed our Freaky Peach Pennsylvania Sour Ale. Finally, the whiskey was steeped with fresh peaches and apricots. With notes of peach, mango, brown sugar and allspice, Pennsylvania Peach is a sweet way to sip through the rest of our Pennsylvania summer. To celebrate this partnership, we're donating $1 from each bottle to @FeedingPA's win-win mission of connecting food-insecure Pennsylvanians with surplus from local farms. #linkinbio to order for Pittsburgh pickup or to get it shipped to your PA or DC home. Available Thurs/July 29! And stay tuned for a celebration here at Tröegs on Thurs/Sept. 2. #Whiskey #WigleWhiskey #Troegs #Cocktails #Beer #Pittsburgh
